"Xinhua All Media+ | Beijing Youth Ice Hockey League Boosts Winter Olympics Enthusiasm -
On December 11th, Xinhua News reported that the player Pang Yao Tian of the Beijing Dreaming ING team took a shot during a match.
On the same day, the 2021-2022 season of the Beijing Youth Ice Hockey Club League continued to compete in major ice rinks in Beijing.
This year's league is divided into the regular season and the playoffs, with participants aged from U6 to U18, divided into competitive and selection groups, attracting nearly 3600 players from 256 representative teams in the city.
After more than a decade of development, the Beijing Youth Ice Hockey Club League has become a platform for Beijing youth ice hockey enthusiasts to sharpen their skills and make friends, and also serves as a source of outstanding players for Beijing youth ice hockey teams and young teams."
"The league plays a driving role in the development of youth ice hockey in Beijing, igniting enthusiasm for the sport ahead of the Winter Olympics, and laying the foundation for the future development of ice hockey in Beijing after the Winter Olympics."